{"title":"Paul Components Clamps Down with New 6-Bolt Boxcar Stem for 7/8″ Bars","link":"https://bikerumor.com/paul-components-new-6-bolt-boxcar-stem-for-7-8-22-2-bars/","date":1697809139000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-pewter-with-lighting-bolt-cross-bar.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem pewter with lighting bolt cross bar\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-pewter-with-lighting-bolt-cross-bar.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-pewter-with-lighting-bolt-cross-bar-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-pewter-with-lighting-bolt-cross-bar-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-pewter-with-lighting-bolt-cross-bar-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-pewter-with-lighting-bolt-cross-bar-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-pewter-with-lighting-bolt-cross-bar-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Blingy bike news alert! Today, Chico’s own Paul Component Engineering, known for its machining wizardry, and for manufacturing beautiful parts for bicycles since 1989, announced their new, limited 7/8″ (22.2mm) Boxcar Stem. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Paul Components, “7/8″ handlebars seem to attract the most abusive riders out there”. so they took their already popular Boxcar stem, and “beefed it up even further”. The new stems, as with all of their Boxcar stems, are made using 2024 alloy because it has a higher fatigue and yield strength than 6061. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-polished-front-e1697757482620.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"653\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-polished-front-e1697757482620-800x653.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem polished front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-polished-front-e1697757482620-800x653.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-polished-front-e1697757482620-297x242.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-polished-front-e1697757482620-120x98.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-polished-front-e1697757482620-768x627.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-polished-front-e1697757482620.jpeg 1024w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Paul Components states that they prefer to let the function and material properties dictate the shape of the product. Sure, some of their products look different, but they say that’s because they want the product to “work as awesome as possible”. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-cross-bar.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-cross-bar-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem silver with cross bar\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-cross-bar-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-cross-bar-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-cross-bar-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-cross-bar-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-cross-bar-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-cross-bar.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-crossbar-2.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-crossbar-2-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem silver with crossbar 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-crossbar-2-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-crossbar-2-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-crossbar-2-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-crossbar-2-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-crossbar-2-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-silver-with-crossbar-2.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So that being said, they made sure that the clamp was extra thick on this limited version. They also added two more high-strength, stainless steel T25 Torx-type faceplate screws. I have to admit, it looks super strong and utilitarian with the extra faceplate screws. They know it’s overkill, but they wanted to make sure this was the last 7/8″ stem you ever buy.   </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>7/8″ Boxcar Origin Story</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>From their website:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>“This stem was designed from the ground up to be stiff, strong, and light. We went through several design iterations and believe we’ve reached the best combination of these three principles. Extensive, real-world, and machine testing have proven this to be one strong stem”.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>“With respect to torsion, the rounded box shape is some 25% stiffer than the competition. As for strength, we ran it through 1,000,000 cycles of above-normal use stress without a single problem.”</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>“How’d we get it so light, while still being so strong? We started with obsessive computer design time, then took the highest quality, American 2024 aerospace alloy and precision machined it to a .002” tolerance (that’s </em>really <em>tight for a stem). We use over 20 different end mills, drills, saws, and taps to make 1 stem”. </em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-front.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-front-800x1200.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem black on BTCHN front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-front-800x1200.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-front-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-front-80x120.jpeg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-front-768x1151.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-front.jpeg 854w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-bike.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-bike-800x1200.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem black on BTCHN bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-bike-800x1200.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-bike-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-bike-80x120.jpeg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-bike-768x1151.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-black-on-BTCHN-bike.jpeg 854w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Features and Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-poilished-studio.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-poilished-studio-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem 35mm poilished studio\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-poilished-studio-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-poilished-studio-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-poilished-studio-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-poilished-studio-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-poilished-studio.jpeg 1024w\" /></a><figcaption>Polished</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-Pewter-studio.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-Pewter-studio-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem 35mm Pewter studio\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-Pewter-studio-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-Pewter-studio-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-Pewter-studio-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-Pewter-studio-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-Pewter-studio.jpeg 1024w\" /></a><figcaption>Pewter Anno</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-purple-studio.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-purple-studio-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem 35mm purple studio\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-purple-studio-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-purple-studio-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-purple-studio-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-purple-studio-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-purple-studio.jpeg 1024w\" /></a><figcaption>Purple Anno</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-silver-studio.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-silver-studio-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem 35mm silver studio\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-silver-studio-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-silver-studio-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-silver-studio-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-silver-studio-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-35mm-silver-studio.jpeg 1024w\" /></a><figcaption>Silver Anno</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-50mm-black-studio.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-50mm-black-studio-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem 50mm black studio\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-50mm-black-studio-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-50mm-black-studio-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-50mm-black-studio-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-50mm-black-studio-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-50mm-black-studio.jpeg 1024w\" /></a><figcaption>Black Anno</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $ 147.50 (all colors) $166.50 (polished)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Colors: Black, Silver, Purple, Pewter, and Polished. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sizes: 35mm and 50mm</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Technical Info</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-Polished-up-close-e1697757925289.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"346\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-Polished-up-close-e1697757925289-800x346.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp New 22.2 Stem Polished up close\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-Polished-up-close-e1697757925289-800x346.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-Polished-up-close-e1697757925289-297x129.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-Polished-up-close-e1697757925289-120x52.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-Polished-up-close-e1697757925289-768x332.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Paul-Comp-New-22.2-Stem-Polished-up-close-e1697757925289.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Weight (including hardware): 180g (35mm), and 201g (50mm) </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Material: American 2024 Aerospace Aluminum</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Finish: Anodized and polished</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Anodized Color: Black, Silver, Purple, and Pewter</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bar Clamp Diameter: 7/8″ (22.2mm)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Length: 35mm or 50mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stem Angle (deg): +/- 0</li>\n\n\n\n<li>S.H.I.S. Steerer clamp Diameter: 28.6</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stack Height: 36mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Torque Settings: Steerer tube: 5nm, Faceplate: 4nm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Face Plate Width: 46mm</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/\">PaulComp.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/paul-components-new-6-bolt-boxcar-stem-for-7-8-22-2-bars/\">Paul Components Clamps Down with New 6-Bolt Boxcar Stem for 7/8″ Bars</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"fd60a4505cb75efbbbbc10a13ad0db509d93722a3bc597f7b5db42363093ff7f","category":"Cycling"}